<br>
One of the foundations of modern liberalism (used in the &quot;classical&quot; sense) is the ability to &quot;agree to disagree&quot;, and therefore recognize that fundamental differences between yourself and other people exist, but that you can each ignore them and work around them.  It is something that people like bin Laden, Wahabbi Muslims, and handfuls of both political and religious extremists here and there cannot grasp.  Without it, democracy could not exist... whenever one actor wins, the other stages a revolt because they cannot live with the results.  It's why so many Third World nations simply cannot function with a democratic government in place.  Its presence in American society is why even people who believe strongly in their religion or ideology can get along without resorting to the sort of action that bin Laden has taken.  People all around you live with beliefs, be they secular or religious, just as strong as bin Laden or the 9/11 hijackers had... the difference is that they don't run around running planes into tall buildings to get their policies enacted. <p>Caledhon TelRana - Champion<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701"><br>
