<br>
Religious zealots in the US don't fly planes into buildings because their religion is not supported by the state and they don't have the support that the groups have over there. Were they given the ability to, there's fundamentalist religious groups here that would do the same things as al qaeda. The issue is not everyday people with strong beliefs, they're a dime a dozen, it's people with strong beliefs with the means to make things happen. Very often that means is money. Depending on what they're trying to accomplish determines how powerful that leader needs to be. Overcoming the inertia of a juggernaut like the US government is a far cry from overthrowing the brand new government of a poor third world country. The latter is realistic for an individual or small group while the former is not. That is why they get overthrown and we do not, not &quot;the ability to get along&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
