<br>
As to the other more on topic point, yeah... people are going to act in their self interest.  But their self interest is not always based purely upon personal advancement... for religious fundamentalists, it is often the advancement of their organization, or their God (as they see it), and for these they will do almost anything.  Even if it may not be the best thing for the person themself, if they believe strongly enough that it is in the best interest of their God or their religion, strongly enough, then they will do things like the old Christian martyrs did, or the Jews who refused to convert during the Inquisition, or the Muslims who fly planes into buildings now... each is an act of supreme faith, there can be no doubt.  Unfortunately faith can be twisted, people can be manipulated, or the basis of the faith can even be corrupt and call upon people to do evil things... but that is not an argument for this thread. <p>Caledhon TelRana - Champion<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701"><br>
