<br>
Law, Government, education, etc.  The powers within the church withheld education from people because, of course, that would lead to questioning the will of god (or what the people were TOLD the will of god was).  A re-birth of education and free thought not seen since the fall of the Roman empire led to the reasonably rapid downfall of the Church's ultimate power.<br>
<br>
Islamic leaders took note and are just trying not make the same mistake.  But it wasn't that long ago that the &quot;west&quot; was in the same grip of an organized religion using its position to gain power.  And believe me, the church is pissed they lost power and are constantly trying to regain it - look at those fruitcakes in the Christian Coalition in the US, it's not *that* far of a stretch from the Islamic fundamentalists.  <br>
<br>
People who vote with the Christian Right (aka the Fundamentalists) are asking that the laws of the church (the &quot;values&quot;) be made into law, so that the church can tell me what is right and wrong and arrest me for not being a good Christian, whether i agree with those values or not.  Sound familiar? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg>TheTribunal.org</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36>Reality Sinks In</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org/">Home</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font> <!-- .. -->
